STEPS TO RUN THE FREELANCER APP:

PRE-REQ:
- Install Node server and NPM:
  Node installer comes with NPM
  https://nodejs.org/en/

- Install Git

1. clone the report from github:
   git clone https://github.com/vaidehinaik/Freelancer.git

2. Install all the required libraries:
  Run NPM INSTALL: In the directory where package.json is present
  cd client_react_redux : npm install
  cd server_express : npm install

3. Bring the backend server up on port 3001:
   cd server_express : npm start

4. Bring the frontend server up on port 3000:
  cd client_react_redux : npm start

5: Your web app will run at http://localhost:3000/

MOCHA Testing:
Install mocha: npm install mocha -g
Install dependencies in backend: chai and chai-http for asserts
cd server_express:
   npm install --save chai
   npm install --save chai-http

cd server_express/test
   npm test
